cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.CY 

This paper is primarily focused on the design and architecture of a communication network, specifically the Tactile Internet, which involves real-time control, touch, and sensing/actuation information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses various aspects of the protocol stack, interfaces, and functional capabilities, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents a case study and evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture, which could be relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the standardization efforts of the IEEE P1918.1 working group, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
